^

^

Press any key to continue . . .
does it ment i have do put it like
deleteitem.class(int,int, 1);? help me out here ploz im so close to killing this stupid error

[/quote]

An integer is a numerical value that does not have a decimal point.

You don’t write int, you write the number.

Example;
NO:
deleteItem(int, int, 1);

YES:
deleteItem(995, getItemSlot(995), 1);

PS: This probably wont work as it just came off the top of my head, it was an example.[/quote]

uhhh.what?
